The paper focuses on open-domain question answering, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves text retrieval and modeling relationships between paragraphs, which suggests the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a likely second choice. The use of a knowledge base and reading comprehension model suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as additional possibilities. Finally, the paper mentions the use of a graph structure, which could fall under the sub-category cs.DL (Deep Learning).
